"HC_CLAIMS_A_01" = "Make your claim anytime right here in the app. You can either do a voice recording or write to us. We will respond to you as soon as we can and keep you updated throughout the process.\n\nHere's how it works:\n* Go to [Make a claim](https://hedvig.page.link/home)\n* Report a claim by telling us what has happened in a voice recording or text\n* We will handle your claim as soon as we can\n\nTo report a claim via e-mail, send your statement to hedvig@hedvig.com and include:\n* Your personal information\n* A statement of the incident\n* Description of damaged items and compensation sought\n* Supporting documents (e.g., receipts, bank statements, photos).\n\nFor security reasons, we cannot assist with reporting a claim or provide case updates over the phone.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_02" = "Once you have reported a claim, our team will get back to you as soon as possible with the next steps. In some cases we might need more information from you to help you further.\n\nSome smaller claims can be handled within minutes in the app. Larger incidents often needs a little more assistance from our service team. If you have any questions about your specific claim, you are always welcome to write to us here in the app.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_03" = "Processing times vary depending on what has happened and how extensive the specific damage is. For larger incidents, it usually takes a little longer. We always aim to provide our assistance as quickly as we can. \n\nIf you have any questions about your case, you are always welcome to write to us here in the app.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_04" = "We compensate based on the specific item's market value. Most items depreciate in value over time and the aim is to leave you in the same financial situation as before the damage. In your terms and conditions, you will find a table showing age deductions for the most common items. A fixed amount of compensation is set for some items.\n\nThe deductible varies depending on the type of damage you have suffered. You can find your deductible in the app or in your insurance policy.\n\nRead more about your insurance policies [here](https://hedvig.page.link/insurances).";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_05" = "Different types of claims may need different types of documentation. In order to speed up the process please provide receipts. Stating the time, date and location of the incident also makes the process faster for you.\n\nAre several items damaged, stolen or lost? Contact us, and we will help send you a simple template where you can give us the details of all items.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_06" = "In the event of a water leak, the necessary steps may vary depending on your location. Initially, it is crucial to promptly address the leak, taking measures to stop its progression and mitigate further damage. We will be assisting you at every stage of managing water damage. \n\nYou can report the claim in the app. Larger and more serious claims will be prioritized. If you prefer calling us reach us on +46 10-45 99 200, Mon–Fri 9-16.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_07" = "Contact our partner Assistancekåren at any time. They will be there quickly if you need road side assistance and/or towing. Our partial and full car insurance covers towing for the most common damage events.\n\nYou can reach Assistancekåren on +46 10 45 99 222, around the clock.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_08" = "When you need help with the removal of vermin or wood pests, you should contact our partner Nomor directly. They will help you with the part of your insurance that covers pest control. Report your claim at nomor.se or by phone 0771-122 300, Mon-Fri 7-17.\n\nThe protection applies to you who have our house or villa insurance. If you live in a rental apartment or condominium, you should contact your landlord or housing association.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_09" = "With our car insurance, you can repair your car at any workshop, get 24/7 roadside assistance and repair stone chips free of charge. If your car breaks down or you have an accident, you can easily file a claim right here in the app, and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\n\nNeed to repair a windshield? Book an appointment directly at [Ryds Bilglas](https://rydsbilglas.se/boka-tid) or [Carglass](https://www.carglass.se/booking).\n\nIf you have had a serious accident and need urgent help –call 112! If several cars are involved, both drivers must report the damage to their respective insurance companies.";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_10" = "We will refer you to the nearest suitable workshop within our network. If you want to choose another workshop, your claims handler needs to approve it first. We also collaborate with workshops such as Ryds Bilglas and Carglass for glass repairs. For stone chips and glass damage abroad, we recommend waiting until you are back in Sweden, but if it is urgent, you can use Carglass even outside Sweden.\n\nBook an appointment for glass repair directly with [Carglass](https://www.carglass.se/booking) or [Ryds Bilglas](https://rydsbilglas.se/boka-tid).";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_11" = "Stone chips are normally covered by the insurance if you have our partial or full insurance. When repairing stone chips, we do not charge any deductible at all. If the entire window needs to be replaced, you will pay a deductible of SEK 2,000. \n\nIf you have partial or full insurance with us, you can go to the workshop directly without reporting the damage to us first. You pay any excess at the workshop. \n\nBook an appointment for glass repair directly at [Carglass](https://www.carglass.se/booking) or [Ryds Bilglas](https://rydsbilglas.se/boka-tid).";
"HC_CLAIMS_A_12" = "We always strive to get better, so if you are not satisfied with the handling of your claim, we encourage you to file a complaint with us. Contact us via the app or email complaints@hedvig.com.";
