"HC_COVERAGE_A_01" = "The insurance covers your spouse or partner and children – as long as they are added to your policy. You can easily add and remove co-insured [here](https://hedvig.page.link/insurances).\n\nThe co-insured is covered by the same conditions as the policyholder. In most cases, the price of the policy will be higher when you add co-insured, as it covers more people.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_02" = "If you want to know more about your insurance with Hedvig, you can find your insurance conditions and your insurance letter [here](https://hedvig.page.link/insurances).\n\nIf you want to read more about any other insurance or purchase another one, you can easily do so here:\n[Home Insurance](https://www.hedvig.com/se-en/insurances/home-insurance)\n[Car Insurance](https://www.hedvig.com/se-en/insurances/car-insurance)\n[Pet Insurance](https://www.hedvig.com/se-en/insurances/pet-insurance)\n[Accident Insurance](https://www.hedvig.com/se-en/insurances/accident)";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_03" = "If an incident has occurred, it is crucial to promptly report the claim to us. This enables us to assess the situation, align it with the terms and conditions of your insurance, and determine eligibility for compensation. In some cases we may need to ask more questions to help you further.\n\nMake a claim [here](https://hedvig.page.link/home).";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_04" = "Our home insurance policies provide coverage for you and up to six additional individuals residing with you, meaning households of 1-7 people.\n\nTo ensure coverage for the people in your household, it's essential to add them as co-insured. Do it [here](https://hedvig.page.link/insurances).\n\nTo sign up for an insurance with us, you must be 18 years or older. However, if you have children under 18 who are not officially registered at your address but regularly reside in your home, you can still include them in your policy. They will be covered when in your care.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_05" = "Yes. The current situation in the world have put many people in difficult situations. We have therefor expanded our coverage to cover refugees staying with our members.\n\nIf you wish to extend your home insurance to cover refugees, send us a message here in the app. This extension is provided at no extra cost.\n\nPlease note that the co-insurance is valid for a duration of 3 months and is applicable to individuals who are not yet officially registered in Sweden. However, it cannot be utilized by members who offer accommodation in exchange for rent or any other form of compensation, such as arrangements with a municipality.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_06" = "Yes! In addition to the travel insurance already included in your home or house insurance, which covers you for 45 days, you can add the extended coverage, Travel Insurance Plus. With this extended coverage, you can choose whether you want it to apply for 45 or 60 days.\n\nTravel Insurance Plus gives you additional coverage, such as cancellation protection, compensation for delays, and rental car deductible reduction. Learn more and get your price [here](https://hedvig.page.link/travel-addon).\n\nGood to know about travel insurance.\nIf you make a visit home to the same destination your travel started from, you need to be home for at least 30 days in between your travels for a new 45 or 60-day period to start.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_07" = "Some travel protection for trips abroad is included in Hedvig’s home insurances. If you have a home insurance you can download a travel certificate [here](https://hedvig.page.link/travelCertificate). The certificate confirms that you are covered by insurance in case something happens to you, which may be necessary in some countries.\n\nDo you need additional coverage for your next trip? With Travel Insurance Plus, you can receive compensation for things like missed activities, delayed luggage, cancellation protection, rental car deductible reduction, and much more. You can also choose whether Travel Insurance Plus should apply for 45 or 60 days. Read more and sign Travel Plus [here](hedvig.page.link/travel-addon).";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_08" = "If the injury occurred during the insurance period and fulfils the criteria to be classified as an accidental injury (bodily injury, involuntary, of sudden external violence/external event and having required medical attention), we can help with compensation for permanent scars based on the scar table. The assessment is usually made 12 months after the wound occurred.\n\nRead more about your accident insurance [here](https://hedvig.page.link/insurances).";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_09" = "Unfortunately, accident insurance does not cover sick leave or loss of income. However, if you have lost your ability to work by at least 50%% due to an accidental injury that is so severe that you cannot work to the same extent as if you had before the injury, the insurance can help with compensation for so-called economic disability.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_10" = "If you or a family member has an accident, Hedvig can compensate you for, among other things, hospitalisation, rehabilitation, therapy and dental injuries. The insurance also protects you if you suffer permanent disability or reduced working capacity as a result of an accident.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_11" = "Read about the fixed deductible [here](https://hedvig.com/se-en/insurances/pet-insurance)";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_12" = "Hedvig offers three different levels of cat and dog insurance, with deductibles of 0 kr, 2 500 kr or 3 500 kr. In addition to the fixed deductible, you have a variable deductible of 15-25 %% of the cost of treatment. You only pay the fixed deductible once per insurance year (12 months), regardless of the number of vet visits.\n\nOur deductibles:\nBasic: 0 kr or 3 500 kr fixed + 25 %% variable\nStandard: 0 kr or 2 500 kr fixed + 25 %% variable\nPremium: 0 kr or 2 500 kr fixed + 15 %% variable\n\nYour fixed deductible will always be 1 000 kr lower than shown above if you first book a digital appointment with FirstVet and are referred to a clinic. You can book unlimited calls with FirstVet at no extra cost.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_13" = "The monthly premium is usually lower if your animal is neutered, as the risk of contracting certain diseases is reduced. If you have neutered your animal after signing up for Hedvig, please contact us.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_14" = "If there is a specific cost or treatment you are considering, we recommend that you contact your veterinarian and ask for a preliminary decision. The vet will then submit the necessary information to us, and we can give a definitive answer regarding your coverage and reimbursement.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_15" = "FirstVet is a digital veterinary clinic where you can get advice from licensed veterinarians. The service is included in our pet insurance and you have unlimited access to veterinary calls at FirstVet at no extra cost.\n\nPlease register Hedvig as your insurance company with FirstVet.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_16" = " ";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_17" = "Traffic insurance is mandatory by law as long as the car is used. It is your responsibility as the owner to ensure that the car has a valid Traffic insurance policy. If the car does not have Traffic insurance, you will have to pay high fees to the Swedish Motor Insurances. You do not need an insurance if the car is cancelled at temporary deregistered.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_18" = "In general, you are not allowed to drive a car that has been temporarily deregistered.\n\nHowever, the Swedish Transport Agency has made exceptions for a journey that is the shortest suitable route to or from the nearest inspection. In this case, the car must be insured against accidents and there must be no unpaid vehicle taxes. You are also not allowed to tow a car that is parked. You can read more on the Swedish Transport Agency's website [here](https://www.transportstyrelsen.se/).";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_19" = "A green card serves as proof that your car has the compulsory traffic insurance required to drive both in Sweden and abroad. Some countries require you to show a green card when driving in the country.\n\nIn most European countries, you do not need a special insurance certificate. However, when driving abroad, you should bring your car registration certificate and your insurance policy, which you can find here in the app under the Insurance tab.\n\nCountries with green card requirements (see an updated list on tff.se):\n\n* Albania\n* Azerbaijan\n* Iran\n* Morocco\n* Moldova\n* North Macedonia\n* Tunisia\n* Turkey\n* Ukraine\n\nContact us in the Hedvig app if you need a green card. The card will be sent to you by post.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_20" = "Hedvig's car insurance is available as traffic insurance, partial insurance and full insurance.\n\nTraffic insurance is required by Swedish law. It covers all personal injury and property damage caused by the car. For example, if you damage another car, your traffic insurance will cover the damage to the other car. \n\nTo get help with damage to your car, you will also need to take out partial or full insurance. Partial insurance includes traffic insurance, but also theft, fire, glass, machinery, rescue and legal protection insurance. Full insurance covers the same as our partial insurance, including traffic insurance, and also includes vehicle damage insurance. \n\nIf you have a newer car with a vehicle damage guarantee, partial insurance is usually enough to get the same coverage as full insurance.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_21" = "If you have misfuelled, do not start the car and contact a workshop immediately to reduce the risk of major damage to the car and engine. Unfortunately, misfuelling is not covered by Hedvig's car insurance.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_22" = "You can switch at any time between traffic, partial and full insurance. The easiest way is to contact us directly here in the app, and we will help you.";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_23" = "Yes! You can always choose a more comprehensive coverage, as long as you don’t already have the maximum protection, or select a higher deductible amount to lower your monthly premium. Click [here](https://hedvig.page.link/change-tier) to update your insurance coverage. \n\nIf you need additional travel protection, you can also add our Travel Plus coverage to your home insurance [here](https://hedvig.page.link/travel-addon).\n";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_24" = "Yes! Since January 8, 2025, ID theft coverage is included in our Home and House insurance with the Standard and Max coverage levels. If you are currently on the Bas coverage level, you can upgrade to Standard or Max [here](https://hedvig.page.link/change-tier).";
"HC_COVERAGE_A_25" = "Yes, for insurances signed or renewed after January 8, 2025, you can increase your base deductible at any time, as long as you don't already have the highest deductible level. Go to [your insurances](https://hedvig.page.link/insurances) and choose ‘Edit your insurance’.\n\nThe deductible level can affect your monthly premium. Choosing a higher deductible can lower your monthly premium, while a lower deductible can increase it.";
