"HC_OTHER_A_01" = "Invite friends to take out their own insurance with Hedvig with your personalized code, and reduce your monthly fee by SEK 10 each time a friend uses the code. Invite as many friends as you like and keep the discount as long as you and your invited friend are Hedvig members.";
"HC_OTHER_A_02" = "No, Hedvig has the same prices whether you buy one or several insurance policies.";
"HC_OTHER_A_03" = "If you need to make a claim, you can do so directly here in the app. You can also email your claim to claims@hedvig.com. Describe what happened, what you are seeking compensation for, where it happened, and include your name and full social security number.\n\nFor other questions, it is easiest to write to us here in the app. You can also reach us by phone on +46 10-45 99 200 during weekdays 9-16. Unfortunately, we cannot handle personal information or answer details about a claim over the phone.";
"HC_OTHER_A_04" = "If you take out a home or car insurance policy with Hedvig, you can choose for us to cancel your old policy for you. In some cases we are not able to cancel it for you. The cancellation date might be too close in time or your current insurance company might want to receive the cancellation directly from you. In this case, you need to cancel the policy yourself. This also applies when you sign a pet insurance with Hedvig. \n\nIf you are adding a new insurance and are unsure whether you need to cancel your old insurance yourself, you can always ask send us a message here in the app.";
"HC_OTHER_Q_01" = "How does Hedvig Forever work?";
"HC_OTHER_Q_02" = "Do I get a discount if I get several insurance policies?";
"HC_OTHER_Q_03" = "How can I get in touch with Hedvig?";
"HC_OTHER_Q_04" = "When do I need to cancel my old insurance?";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_01" = "Monthly payments are made by digital direct debit via our partner Trustly. If you have not already connected your direct debit, you can easily do so [here](https://hedvig.page.link/payments). To link your direct debit, you need a Swedish personal number and a mobile BankId. It can take up to 1-3 banking days to approve your linked bankgiro. You can see it in the app as soon as it is approved.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_02" = "As the withdrawal is made at the end of each month, this means that money can be withdrawn even if the insurance policy is terminated. You only pay for the days that the policy has been active. \n\nExample: Your policy was terminated on June 15. On June 27, the last payment is deducted for the days in June that the policy was active. You only pay for the period between June 1 and 15.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_03" = "To connect your payment you need a mobile BankID. Digital direct debit is easily connected via the Hedvig app, not through your bank.  \n\nIf you cannot connect your direct debit via the Hedvig app, it may be that your bank has a block on digital direct debit. Contact your bank for more information. Are you still having problems connecting your payments? Send us a message here in the app.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_04" = "You can access up to 12 months of payment history [here](https://hedvig.page.link/payments). You can easily see which insurances you have paid for and whether you have had any active discounts. \n\nDo you need to see payments made earlier than 12 months ago? Write to us here in the app.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_05" = "It is only possible to pay for Hedvig by digital direct debit. The following banks accept digital direct debit:\n\n* Nordea\n* SEB\n* Swedbank & Sparbankerna\n* Skandiabanken\n* Handelsbanken\n* Danske Bank\n* ICA Banken\n* Länsförsäkringar Bank";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_06" = "You can easily access all the details of your payments [here](https://hedvig.page.link/payments). If we have or will charge more than your expected monthly price, it may be due to one of the following:\n* You've added a policy or made a change to your existing policy, such as adding a co-insured person or moving into a larger home.\n* Your discount code has expired during a current month, so the amount has been adjusted on the next payment.\n* Your insurance policy is renewed after one year and it is common for the price to increase. Renewals are always notified in advance.\n* You have a missed payment, which will be included in the next payment. This can happen if you are a new member and you sign a digital direct debit close to the first payment (on the 27th) and the connection has not yet gone through.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_07" = "You can easily see all the details of your payment [here](https://hedvig.page.link/payments). If we have charged less than your expected monthly cost, it may be due to one of the following:\n* If your policy starts in the middle of a month, the first payment may be less than your monthly price, as you only pay for the days of the current month that you have an active policy.\n* You have cancelled a policy or changed something in your existing policy, such as removing a co-insured person or moving to a smaller home.\n* A discount has been activated during a current month. Example: a friend signed up using your Hedvig Forever code.\n\nRead more about Hedvig Forever [here](https://hedvig.page.link/forever)";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_08" = "You can pay by digital direct debit if you have one of the following banks:\n\n* Nordea\n* SEB\n* Swedbank & Sparbankerna\n* Skandiabanken\n* Handelsbanken\n* Danske Bank\n* ICA Banken\n* Länsförsäkringar Bank";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_09" = "Your price may have changed due to the renewal of your policy. This happens once a year and it is common for the price to be adjusted. This could be because something has changed in your life during the year or because inflation has changed.\n\nWe evaluate our prices every year to make sure that no one pays too much or too little. Our aim is always to set prices that are as fair and accurate as possible.\n\nIf your price has changed during a current policy year, it may be because you have added, removed or changed something in your policies. It could also be because a time-limited discount has expired.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_10" = "Make sure your digital direct debit is connected. You can do this easily [here](https://hedvig.page.link/payments). If you haven't been charged, it may be due to one of the following:\n* The date of the payment has been affected by a public holiday, the date of the payment is postponed to the next day of the week.\n* Insufficient funds. Make sure that you have the enough balance on the 27th of every month to cover each payment. Three additional attempts will be made in the following weekdays.\n* If you are a new member and have signed a digital direct debit close to the first payment (on the 27th), the connection may not yet have gone through. The missed amount will be added to the next month's payment.\n\nNot an answer to your question? Send us a message here in the app.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_11" = "Yes, you can lower your monthly premium for your home insurance by increasing your deductible. Go to [insurance](https://hedvig.page.link/insurances) to change your deductible. You can also reduce your monthly premium with Hedvig Forever. Invite friends to sign up with Hedvig, and both you and your invited friend will get a 10 SEK/month discount as soon as they sign an insurance with your personal code. You can invite as many friends as you like. Invite enough people, and you could reduce your premium to as low as 0 SEK. You keep the discount as long as you and your invited friends remain insured with Hedvig.\n \nGet started with your Hedvig Forever discount code [here](https://hedvig.page.link/forever)";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_12" = "We aim to give you the right price from the start so that you keep the same price for as long as possible. To make sure that no one contributes too little or too much to the common claims pool, we constantly evaluate our prices. If your price changes, we'll let you know 30 days in advance.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_13" = "If you have a protected identity, you will not be able to connect your payment via digital direct debit. This is due to the rules and procedures of our payment partner Trustly, which handles all our payments.\n\nSince we only accept direct debit as payment method, we will not be able to insure you at this time. Write us a message here in the app if you have further questions.";
"HC_PAYMENTS_A_14" = "If you are not registered in Sweden, you will not be able to connect your payment via direct debit. This is due to the rules and procedures of our payment partner Trustly, which handles all our payments.\n\nSince we only accept direct debit as payment method, we will not be able to insure you at this time. Write us a message here in the app if you have further questions.";
